---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { Reveal } from '../components/Reveal';

const title = "Private Retreat — Body, Mind & Soul Therapy";
const description = "A fully personalised one-on-one healing retreat in Bali, Turkey, or where you are. Nine integrated modalities, tailored to your body and your life.";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <section class="py-section-y px-section-x max-w-7xl mx-auto">
    <Reveal client:load>
      <div class="text-center mb-24">
        <span class="text-sm font-medium tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-soil-muted mb-8 block">Private & Personalised</span>
        <h1 class="text-6xl md:text-8xl font-display mb-12 text-soil leading-tight">A private retreat built around you.</h1>
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-soil-muted max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-16 leading-relaxed">
          One practitioner. Nine integrated modalities. A program designed for the person you actually are — and, increasingly, for the place you actually need it to happen.
        </p>
        <a href="https://tidycal.com/miro-kloosterman/15-minute-meeting" class="btn-primary">Book a free discovery call</a>
      </div>
    </Reveal>

    <div class="mt-32 space-y-40">
      <Reveal client:load>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-24 items-center">
          <div class="order-2 lg:order-1">
            <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display mb-10 text-soil">No two people are the same. Neither are two retreats.</h2>
            <div class="space-y-8 text-lg text-soil-muted leading-relaxed">
              <p>I don't run a standard program. I never have. Before you arrive — or before I arrive — we spend time together, sometimes weeks, understanding what you're actually dealing with, what your body is doing, what your life looks like, and what you're ready for. Only then do I start building your retreat.</p>
              <p>By the time the first day begins, the program is already designed around you. And it keeps adjusting as we go, because the body in front of me on day four is not the same body I met on day one.</p>
              <p>The support doesn't end when you leave — or when I do. I stay with you for at least a month afterwards, usually longer, while you integrate what moved and carry the work back into your real life.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="order-1 lg:order-2 aspect-square rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-tactile lg:translate-x-12">
            <img src="https://picsum.photos/seed/retreat-1/1000/1000" alt="Retreat Space" class="object-cover w-full h-full scale-105 hover:scale-100 transition-transform duration-1000" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </Reveal>

      <Reveal client:load>
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display mb-16 text-center text-soil">Where the retreat happens.</h2>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-12">
          <div class="service-card">
            <h3 class="text-3xl font-display">Bali</h3>
            <p class="text-soil-muted">Most of this practice grew up here. Bali holds the work in a particular way — the land, the water, the pace, the culture around healing. For clients who want the full immersion, Bali is still the first place I'd recommend.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="service-card lg:translate-y-12">
            <h3 class="text-3xl font-display">Turkey</h3>
            <p class="text-soil-muted">I also run private retreats in Turkey, where my partner Damla Yaku is based. Different landscape, different quality of stillness, same depth of work. When water therapy is central, Turkey often becomes the right choice.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="service-card">
            <h3 class="text-3xl font-display">Where you are</h3>
            <p class="text-soil-muted">For private clients who can't travel — or who need the work to happen in their own environment — I travel. I've held retreats in villas, homes, and locations around the world when the fit is right and the costs are covered.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-xl text-center mt-24 max-w-2xl mx-auto text-soil-muted italic">Duration is the same story — it's built around you. Some clients need three days. Some need two weeks. Some need something longer. We figure that out together in the discovery call.</p>
      </Reveal>

      <Reveal client:load>
        <div class="bg-surface-container-low p-12 md:p-24 rounded-xl shadow-tactile">
          <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display mb-12 text-center text-soil">The work itself.</h2>
          <p class="text-xl mb-16 text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto text-soil-muted">Every retreat draws from the nine modalities I've trained in. Which ones you experience depends entirely on what you need. A typical retreat includes a combination of:</p>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-x-20 gap-y-6 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
            {[
              "Health and lifestyle coaching",
              "Detoxing and nutrition work",
              "Breathwork (including trauma-release sessions)",
              "Body Reset therapy for structural pain",
              "Chi Core Release massage (Chi Nei Tsang)",
              "Intuitive massage",
              "Harmonic Flow Aquatic Healing Arts (water therapy)",
              "Reiki",
              "Hypnotherapy",
              "Reconnecting with your inner child and play"
            ].map(item => (
              <div class="flex items-center gap-4 text-lg text-soil">
                <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-secondary"></div>
                <span>{item}</span>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      </Reveal>

      <Reveal client:load>
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
          <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display mb-16 text-center text-soil">This is for you if…</h2>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-x-16 gap-y-10">
            {[
              "You are dealing with something deep and know a weekend workshop won't touch it",
              "You want a program designed around your actual body, not a pre-built curriculum",
              "You've been carrying chronic illness, grief, burnout, or trauma",
              "You want privacy and one-on-one attention, not a group container",
              "You can travel to Bali or Turkey — or you need the work to come to you",
              "The length, the place, and the depth can all be shaped around what you need"
            ].map(item => (
              <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
                <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-secondary/20 flex items-center justify-center mt-1 flex-shrink-0">
                  <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-secondary"></div>
                </div>
                <p class="text-lg text-soil-muted leading-snug">{item}</p>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      </Reveal>

      <Reveal client:load>
        <div class="text-center bg-surface-container-highest p-16 rounded-xl relative overflow-hidden">
          <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-64 h-64 bg-primary/5 rounded-full -translate-y-1/2 translate-x-1/2"></div>
          <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display mb-8 text-soil">Investment.</h2>
          <p class="text-xl text-soil-muted max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-16 leading-relaxed">
            Every private retreat is built from scratch, so the investment is different for every client. It depends on the length of your stay, the depth of the work, where we run it, what your body and situation call for, and what's possible for you.
          </p>
          <a href="https://tidycal.com/miro-kloosterman/15-minute-meeting" class="btn-primary">Book a free discovery call</a>
        </div>
      </Reveal>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
